      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0575P0-05892'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0575P0_19961120_GCR_193' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble and learned Lord said: In moving Amendment No. 33 I speak also to Amendment No. 34. These are technical amendments. Section 84 of the <a href="/acts/supreme-court-act-1981">Supreme Court Act</a> is relevant both to rule-making powers for civil and criminal cases in the Supreme Court, and to other special rules applying to Supreme Court proceedings&#x2014;that is, family proceeding rules made by other committees under other enactments. These amendments contain the powers of the different rule authorities to apply rules made by other rule committees if so desired. Their effect is to provide special rules, rules made by any committee or rule-making body other than the civil procedure rule committee and the Crown Court rule committee. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0575P0-05893'>
